news.title: Will bear structural audit cost of Chintels Paradiso towers, says builder
news.para: On February 14, the town and country planning department had written to the director of IIT-Delhi for conducting an audit of the buildings at Paradiso, where a vertical collapse of five living rooms led to the deaths of two residents on February 10.

news.title: Chintels Paradiso residents hold protest march, demand CBI inquiry
news.para: The protesters have demanded "immediate arrest" of the promoters and directors of Chintels India Ltd and the government officials who issued occupation certificates (OC) for the apartments. They were supported by residents of adjoining housing societies.

news.title: MMRDA halts Mumbai's salt pans development blueprint, no scrapping order
news.para: “We have not gone ahead with the plan to appoint a consultant. The bids have not been processed and the tender will lapse in some days. However, so far, no formal orders to scrap the plan have been issued,” said an official.

news.title: For four years, 114 buildings 'unsafe', but Noida authority yet to take any action
news.para: In July 2018, nine persons died when two buildings — a new one and another being constructed — collapsed in Shahberi village of Dadri.

news.title: Gurugram: Registration of sale deeds of all projects of Chintels to be stopped
news.para: “In light of this incident at Chintel Paradiso, all sub-registrars have been directed to refrain from registering any document related to any property in projects developed by Chintels India Ltd, Chintels Exports Pvt Ltd, Ashok Solomon and Intels India Pvt Ltd,” the letter read.

news.title: Haryana government to amend building bylaws
news.para: Senior officials in the chief minister's office (CMO) said work towards this direction has already begun and there is a possibility of bringing some changes ahead of the assembly session.

news.title: IIFL Home Finance to get $68 million ADB loans
news.para: The funding comprises a direct ADB loan of $58 million and another $10 million concessional loan from the Canadian Climate Fund. The Canadian fund will also be routed through ADB.

news.title: Puravankara's sales bookings up 17% to Rs 666 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: According to its investors presentation, Puravankara sold 0.99 million square feet area during October-December 2021-22 as against 0.91 million square feet area in the year-ago period.

news.title: GIC to pick up three million sq ft in Bengaluru's Bharatiya City for Rs 2,800 crore
news.para: The deal will see GIC picking up 3 million sq ft of commercial assets in Bhartiya City, a 125-acre township project, from the builder, along with some revenue from its facility management business.

news.title: DS Kulkarni's wife gets bail in Kolhapur misappropriation of funds case
news.para: A case against 62-year-old Hemanti Kulkarni was registered at Kolhapur’s Rajarampuri police station in 2017 over misappropriation of funds collected and deposited by the investors from Kolhapur.

news.title: RBI to get its own office space at Goa's Patto Plaza in three years
news.para: The RBI building is expected to be completed in three years and could be designed as per Indian Green Building Council (IGBC) norms, officials said.

news.title: Forest department admits land deals in Chikhaldara against rules
news.para: The Maharashtra government, state forest department, and Melghat Tiger Reserve’s (MTR) admission comes on an affidavit filed before the Supreme Court’s Central Empowered Committee (CEC) recently.

news.title: Chandigarh: 12 freehold sites to be up for e-auction from March 14 to 16
news.para: The two nursing home sites are in Sector 51, whereas 10 commercial sites, including booth and SCO are in sectors 33, 36, 39, 42 and 44. Earlier, the estate office started the process of e-auction of eight residential sites on freehold basis.

news.title: Kolkata: Owners can view all property bills at a go on updated portal
news.para: A KMC assessment department official said previously, there were three tabs to view different types of assessment bills: outstanding bills, fresh/supplementary bills and periodic demands (PD) bills.

news.title: Life Mission third phase progressing in Kochi district
news.para: In the third phase, according to former district mission coordinator Ernest C Thomas, the beneficiaries are both landless and those who do not own a house.
